  "text": "Round of 16 · 7 July 2026. Final score: Argentina 3–2 Egypt. Argentina produced a stunning comeback, turning a two-goal deficit into a stoppage-time victory.\n\nThe reigning champions stared elimination in the face, two goals down and with their talisman's penalty already saved.\n\nThe goals, in sequence: 46′ Omar Ibrahim — 0–1; 67′ Zico — 0–2; 79′ Cristian Romero — 1–2; 84′ Lionel Messi — 2–2; 94′ Enzo Fernández — 3–2. That is 5 goals in all, Argentina accounting for 3 and Egypt 2.\n\nOmar Ibrahim and Zico had Egypt dreaming at 2-0, and Lionel Messi even saw a penalty saved by an inspired Mohamed Shobeir. Then the tie turned on its head: Cristian Romero powered in a header from Messi's cross, before Messi himself pounced on a loose ball for his 21st career World Cup goal. In the second minute of stoppage time, Enzo Fernández arrived with a lung-busting run to head Lautaro Martínez's cross into the top corner. Champions find a way, and Argentina — through sheer force of Messi's will — found one when it mattered most.\n\nMomentum, as ever in the knockouts, proved a fragile and fleeting thing.\n\nFor the record, Argentina advanced. Goal, team and minute for every event above are Merkle-proven on Solana devnet via TxLINE; the scorer names are attributed from public match reports and aligned to the verified goals by team and order. Nothing here rests on the commentator's word alone.",
